na Vigyan to add to its prestige. All laboratories have latest equipments to help the students in their curricular works.\r\n\r\nSome of the instruments that deserve a mention are Spirometer, Kymoraph, ECG machine, Response time Analyzer, instruments for animal studies, X-ray and Sonography machines, Centrifuge machine; Soxlet apparatus, Ovens, Furnaces etc.\r\n\r\n<h3>Museums</h3>\r\nAll departments have exquisite models and charts that make up a knowledgeable museum. The students are explained the details of various Ayurvedic topics with help of these invaluable assets. Mummified bodies, skeletons, models of various organs, specimens, body system models, specially prepared charts, poisonous drug specimens, lethal weapons set, models of asphyxial death, water purification center model, sewage disposal model, sanitation models, rare Ayurvedic herbs and their photographs are some of the distinct features of the museums.\r\n\r\n<h3>Departmental Library</h3>\r\nThe departmental libraries have good number of subject related reference books. Staff & students avail this at hand facility day to day.\r\n\r\nThe College houses a well-equipped and spacious library. Students make the best use of the library facilities to fulfill their academic and research requirements. The books range from thousands of years old classics up to latest editions of modern medical volumes. Peer reviewed journals & standard periodicals are obtained and added to the previous collection. The silent and peaceful atmosphere of the library ensures a studious ambiance.\r\n\r\n<h3>Herbal Garden</h3>\r\nThe College boasts of a well - planned herbal garden that includes several extinct and rare species of flora. Total no. of species are more than 294 including rare species whereas total no. of medicinal plants are more than 1125. The students are motivated to take benefit of this garden to identify the species and to understand the morphological characterization of medicinal plants. UG and PG students from different college/ institutes, school students and common people visit herbal garden for identification of various plants on regular basis. Some of the plant products are also used for day to day preparation of herbal medicine.','Campus & Infrastructure','','inherit','closed','closed','','183-revision-v1','','','2017-09-21 11:57:21','2017-09-21 06:27:21','',183,'http://localhost/wordpress/2017/09/21/183-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0);
